<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>bed of roses • rose bed</xh5><p> <i>bed of roses</i>—(usually negat.) said of a pleasant, easy condition of life: Post war Hungary was no <u>bed of roses</u>. Political oppression permeated every facet of life.... <i>Cf.: bed of thorns</i>—said of a situation of anxiety and apprehension: It was a <u>bed of thorns</u> every hour of every day all through the making of the film.</p><p> <i>rose bed—</i>a flowerbed of roses: Since I cannot separate lavender from roses in my mind, I plant clumps of it around my <u>rose beds</u>.</p> </entry>
